  "texts": [
    "LLMs could assist developers in writing, refactoring, and optimizing quantum code, potentially lowering the barrier to entry for quantum software development and accelerating the development process (see Section 4.7).",
    "However, challenges in using large language models (LLMs) for software development include bias and inaccuracy in generated code, security risks from suggesting vulnerable patterns, and limitations in contextual understanding, which can lead to integration issues within complex projects.",
    "Additionally, there are ethical and legal concerns around intellectual property, especially when LLMs may reproduce licensed code.",
    "Developers also face a learning curve in effectively using these tools, and integration into existing development workflows, such as CI/CD pipelines, remains a challenge.",
    "Finally, trust in AI-generated code requires careful human oversight to ensure reliability."
  ],
